rComments: Teaching was ok, exams were fair, homeworks were lengthy and pointless. Not very helpful during office hours. On a personal level, he leaves a lot to be desired.

This is not, by any means, a difficult class. Exams are fair and relatively easy. Shiv's homework can be a bit confusing and lengthy at times, though. You can tell he enjoys teaching. I'd suggest going to lecture, since not all the material is in the book. Take halfway decent notes and do the homework and you'll be fine.
